tool_description: A collection of methods that returns various financial data for a requested company including SEC Filings, balance sheets, financial ratios , company look-up utilities and more.
name: SEC Filings
title: SEC Filings

api_list.name: Trending Stocks
api_list.description: Returns the top trending stocks on Last10K.com right now with the most viewed 10-K / 20-F / 40-F Annual Reports and 10-Q Quarterly SEC Filings. View live data at: https://last10k.com/stock-screeners/trending
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://last10k-company-v1.p.rapidapi.com/v1/app/analytics"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "last10k-company-v1.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: Items
api_list.description: Returns the content of each item in an entire 10-K Annual Report

api_list.name: Operations
api_list.description: Returns a company's most recent statement of operations showing how they balance costs with revenue

optional_parameters.name: filingOrder
optional_parameters.description: Retrieve an older financial statement by specifying number of filings to go back. For example, to retrieve the second to most recent filing, specify a filingOrder value of 1. By default, the most recent filing is returned (filingOrder = 0)

api_list.name: Income
api_list.description: Returns a company's most recent income statement detailing what they earn for providing their goods and services OR a statement of loss explaining where lost income occurred

optional_parameters.name: filingorder
optional_parameters.description: Retrieve an older financial statement by specifying number of filings to go back. For example, to retrieve the 10-K filed last year, specify a filingOrder value of 1. By default, the most recent filing is returned (filingOrder = 0)

api_list.name: Manager Ownership
api_list.description: Returns institutional managers positions in a stock including the number of managers that sold, increased, decreased and added a stock to their portfolio by comparing current and previous 13F SEC Filings

api_list.name: Manager Holdings
api_list.description: Returns an institutional manager's quarterly portfolio holdings including new, sold and changed positions by comparing current and previous 13F SEC Filings

api_list.name: Insider Trades
api_list.description:
Returns an aggregated and summarized collection of the most recent BUY, SELL and OPTION EXERCISE insider trades filed with Form 4 SEC Filings.

Visit [https://last10k.com/stock-screeners/insider-trading](https://last10k.com/stock-screeners/insider-trading) to view this data as a web page.

optional_parameters.name: ticker
optional_parameters.description: Publicly traded company's stock symbol. If not specified in the request, the endpoint will return insider trades for all companies on the most recent trading day,

api_list.name: Financial Statements & Disclosures
api_list.description:
Returns a list of financial statements and disclosures from a company's Annual or Quarterly report.

Use the CIK and Accession Number values returned from the SEC Filings endpoint for this endpoint's Request Parameters.

api_list.name: Cash Flows
api_list.description: Returns a company's most recent cash flow statement showing the amount of cash used and generated

optional_parameters.name: filingOrder
optional_parameters.description: Retrieve an older financial statement by specifying number of filings to go back. For example, to retrieve the second to most recent filing, specify a filingOrder value of 1. By default, the most recent filing is returned (filingOrder = 0)

api_list.name: SEC Filings
api_list.description: Returns a list of SEC Filings for the requested company.

required_parameters.name: identifier
required_parameters.description: Publicly traded company's stock symbol or Central Index Key (CIK)

api_list.name: Late SEC Filings
api_list.description: Returns recent 8-K Material Event SEC Filings made after the 5:30pm EST deadline on the previous filing day. The feed is updated live on Monday mornings because these filings do not become publicly available until Monday at 6am EST.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://last10k-company-v1.p.rapidapi.com/v1/company/late-filings"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "last10k-company-v1.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
